<td class="mbox-text plainlist">Wikimedia Commons has media related to <i><b><a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:Search/Cognitive_neuroscience" class="extiw" title="commons:Special:Search/Cognitive neuroscience">Cognitive neuroscience</a></b></i>.</td></tr></tbody></table><div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable relarticle mainarticle">The main article for this <a href="/wiki/Help:Categories" title="Help:Categories">category</a> is <b><a href="/wiki/Cognitive_neuroscience" title="Cognitive neuroscience">Cognitive neuroscience</a></b>.</div>
<p><b>Cognitive neuroscience</b> is an academic field concerned with the scientific study of biological mechanisms underlying <a href="/wiki/Cognition" title="Cognition">cognition</a>, with a specific focus on the neural substrates of mental processes and their behavioral manifestations.  It addresses the questions of how psychological/cognitive functions are produced by the <a href="/wiki/Biological_neural_network" class="mw-redirect" title="Biological neural network">neural circuitry</a>.
</p>




